**Legal Calculus is my gift to the world — created for every person who has ever walked into a courtroom alone and felt the system wasn’t built for them.**

Too many people lose not because they are wrong, but because they are out‑resourced, out‑maneuvered, or simply never taught how procedure works. Justice should not depend on money, connections, or luck. It should depend on clarity, truth, and a fair process.

That’s why I built Legal Calculus.

It is a free, open, educational system designed to help people understand the structure of litigation — how to preserve evidence, organize facts, and build a clean, appeal‑ready record. It does not replace lawyers. It does not give legal advice. It teaches the public what the system never taught them.

Because when people understand procedure, they gain power.  
When they can document retaliation, they gain protection.  
When they can build a record, they gain a voice.

This work is for the whistleblower who stood alone.  
For the worker who was silenced.  
For the parent fighting for stability.  
For the person who had no choice but to represent themselves.  
